        text: 'The earlier sections made clear that the mind shapes the body\'s health more than people admit, so it is worth laying out the full mind-body link as it relates to TMS.\n\nThe mind can act on the heart and blood vessels in dangerous ways. Stroke and death are on the list of risks. None of it comes from a physical cause, and that is the strange part. The mind is doing it, but how?\n\nThe mind holds the conscious and unconscious thoughts that guide behavior and expectation.\n\nThe autonomic nervous system kicks in when brain chemistry tips out of balance, and the body responds in uneven ways. Picture a moment when you lose a job or work turns tense. The mind can cut the brain off from oxygen through the heart, and a stroke follows.\n\nThe immune system is another place the mind acts directly. The immune system guards the body from outside and inside threats. It used to be seen as running on its own, but newer research shows the mind can shape it. There are cases where people feel pain or fall sick because their mind connected an event to the reaction. A useful example: dirty water brings cholera only with steady exposure, but once the mind knows the usual response, it can replay that response after a small dose that would not normally cause illness.\n\nThe mind can also push the immune system to do more. There are cases where people get well without medicine because the mind nudged the system to fight harder.\n\nThe mind-body link shows up in many other places. The mind can drive acne, warts, or a weak bowel that cannot hold spicy food or milk. The role of the mind gets downplayed, and that is a shame, because leaning on it would help a lot more people.'
